'''維吉尼亞·伊詩曼·強生'''<ref name=nytimesobit>{{cite news | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/26/us/virginia-johnson-masterss-collaborator-in-sex-research-dies-at-88.html?pagewanted=all | title = Virginia Johnson, Widely Published Collaborator in Sex Research, Dies at 88 | work = [[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] | first = Margalit | last = Fox | date = July 25, 2013 | accessdate = October 11, 2013 | archive-date = 2018-06-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180628190138/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/26/us/virginia-johnson-masterss-collaborator-in-sex-research-dies-at-88.html?pagewanted=all | dead-url = no }}</ref> （{{lang-en|Virginia Eshelman Johnson}}，{{bd|1925年|2月11日|2013年|7月24日|catIdx=Johnson, Virginia}}），<ref name=guardianobit>{{cite news | title = Virginia Johnson Obituary | url = https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2013/jul/28/virginia-johnson | first = Suzie | last = Hayman | work = [[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] | location = UK | date = July 28, 2013 | accessdate = October 11, 2013 | archive-date = 2017-05-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170501130539/https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2013/jul/28/virginia-johnson | dead-url = no }}</ref> 生於美國[[密蘇里州|密蘇里州]][[斯普林菲尔德_(密苏里州)|春田市]]，性學家與心理學家，與[[威廉·麥斯特|威廉·麥斯特]]（William Howell Masters）組成的[[麥斯特與強生|麥斯特與強生]]性學研究小組，也是因此而被世人熟知。<ref>[https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F10C13FE3F5C1B7493C5AB178FD85F448785F9 "Craftsmen of Sexuality; William H. Masters Virginia E. Johnson"] {{Wayback|url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F10C13FE3F5C1B7493C5AB178FD85F448785F9 |date=20131013122805 }}.  ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]''.</ref> 从1957年开始直到20世纪90年代，她和[[威廉·麥斯特|威廉·麥斯特]]一同对[[人类性反应周期|人类性反应]]的实质以及[[性功能障碍|性功能障碍]]的治疗开展研究，并成为该领域的先驱。

==早年==
弗吉尼亚·约翰逊出生于[[密苏里州|密苏里州]][[斯普林菲尔德|斯普林菲尔德]]，她是艾德娜·伊万斯和赫歇尔·哈里·埃谢尔曼的女儿，父亲赫歇尔是个农场主。<ref name=guardianobit /><ref name=mastersofsexpp7-8-650>{{cite book | title=Masters of Sex: The Life and Times of William Masters and Virginia Johnson, the Couple Who Taught America How to Love | first=Thomas | last=Maier | year=2010 | publisher=ReadHowYouWant <!--spelld solid--> | isbn=978-1458767516 | pages=7, 8, 650 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iVlKkabgfEUC&pg=PA8 | access-date=2017-12-05 | archive-date=2016-04-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160418064435/https://books.google.com/books?id=iVlKkabgfEUC&pg=PA8 | dead-url=no }}</ref> 她的祖父母是[[耶稣基督后期圣徒教会|耶稣基督后期圣徒教会]]成员，她的父亲的祖先是[[黑森|黑森]]人。<ref name=mastersofsexpp7-8-650/> 弗吉尼亚一家人在她五岁那年搬迁到[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]帕罗奥图，他父亲在当地一家医院担任场地管理员。后来这一家人又来到了[[密苏里州|密苏里州]]，并开始农场生活。<ref name=guardianobit /> 16岁的弗吉尼亚被家乡的杜利大学录取，但她中途辍学后在[[密苏里州|密苏里州]]保险局工作了四年。<ref name=guardianobit /> 她最终还是回到校园，先后在[[密苏里大学|密苏里大学]]和堪萨斯音乐学院学习，[[二战|二战]]时期她作为一名乐队歌手，开启了自己的音乐职业生涯。<ref name=guardianobit /> 在她为斯普林菲尔德的[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KWTO_(AM) KWTO] {{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KWTO_(AM) |date=20171010090523 }}广播电台演唱乡村歌曲期间，她使用了“弗吉尼亚·吉布森”这一艺名。<ref name=nytimesobit />

弗吉尼亚之后在[[密苏里州|密苏里州]][[圣路易斯|圣路易斯]]的“圣路易斯日报”担任商业板块作家。<ref name=guardianobit /> 退出歌坛后，弗吉尼亚就读于[[圣路易斯华盛顿大学|圣路易斯华盛顿大学]]，主修[[社会学|社会学]]，<ref name=guardianobit /> 但并未取得该学科的学位。<ref name=missouriwomen>{{cite web|title=Virginia Johnson|url=http://missouriwomen.org/category/women/virginia-johnson/|publisher=Missouri Women|accessdate=2017-12-05|archive-date=2017-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206140100/https://missouriwomen.org/category/women/virginia-johnson/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==性学著作==
{{主条目|麥斯特與強生}}
约翰逊和[[威廉·麥斯特|威廉·麥斯特]]初识于1957年，她被马斯特斯聘为研究助手，在圣路易斯的华盛顿大学妇产科系工作。在约翰逊给他担任助手的这段时间里，马斯特斯在医学术语，疗法，以及研究等方面对她进行了培训。<ref name=missouriwomen/> 他们共同研发了一种类似[[测谎仪|测谎机]]的仪器，用来监测人类的[[性刺激|性刺激]]。马斯特斯和约翰逊使用这些工具，观察了约700名男性和女性的[[性行为|性行为]]，这些志愿者同意在马斯特斯的实验室里和其他参与者性交或者[[自慰|自慰]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Masters and Johnson|url=http://health.howstuffworks.com/sexual-health/sexuality/masters-and-johnson-dictionary.htm|work=Discovery Health|publisher=Sinclair Intimacy Institute|accessdate=2017-12-05|archive-date=2013-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130413060309/http://health.howstuffworks.com/sexual-health/sexuality/masters-and-johnson-dictionary.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 通过观察这些对象，约翰逊帮助马斯特斯确定性反应的四个阶段，也就是所谓的[[人类性反应周期|人类性反应周期]]。这个周期分为兴奋期，持续期，高潮期，和消退期。<ref>{{cite web|title=Four Stages of the Sexual Response Cycle|url=https://www.boundless.com/psychology/gender-development-and-sexuality/physiology-sex/four-stages-sexual-response-cycle/|work=Boundless|accessdate=2013-04-29|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130628193917/https://www.boundless.com/psychology/gender-development-and-sexuality/physiology-sex/four-stages-sexual-response-cycle/|archivedate=2013-06-28|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 1964年，马斯特斯和约翰逊在[[圣路易斯|圣路易斯]]建立了他们自己独立的[[非盈利|非盈利]]研究机构，机构名为生殖生物学基金会，该机构在1978年更名为马斯特斯与约翰逊研究所。

2009年4月，托马斯·迈尔在一篇刊登在《[[科学美国人|科学美国人]]》杂志的报道中称道，马斯特斯与约翰逊研究所曾于1968至1977年开展过试图把同性恋者变为异性恋者的项目，约翰逊对于该项目持有强烈的保留态度。<ref>Maier, Thomas (April 22, 2009). [http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?id=homosexuality-cure-masters-johnson "Can Psychiatrists Really 'Cure' Homosexuality?{{spaced ndash}} Masters and Johnson Claimed to Convert Gays to Heterosexuality in a 1979 Book. But Did They?"].  ''[[Scientific_American|Scientific American]]''.  Retrieved August 10, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite book | author = [[William_H._Masters|Masters, William H.]]; Johnson, Virginia E. |title = Homosexuality in Perspective |year = 1982 | origyear = first published 1979 |publisher = [[Bantam_Books|Bantam Books]] |location = Toronto; New York |isbn = 978-0-553-20809-2}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last=Schwartz | first=MF | author2=Masters, WH | title=The Masters and Johnson treatment program for dissatisfied homosexual men | journal=[[American_Journal_of_Psychiatry|American Journal of Psychiatry]] | volume=141 | pages=173–181 | url=http://ajp.psychiatryonline.org/cgi/content/abstract/141/2/173 | pmid=6691475 | issue=2 | date=February 1, 1984 | access-date=2017-12-05 | archive-date=2011-09-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927062025/http://ajp.psychiatryonline.org/cgi/content/abstract/141/2/173 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==个人生活==
约翰逊二十出头的时候曾嫁给一名密苏里州的政客，<ref name=guardianobit />这段婚姻只持续了2天。<ref name=nytimesobit /> 后来她又和一名大她很多的律师结婚，可也是以离婚收场。<ref name=nytimesobit /> 1950年她嫁给乐队领队乔治·约翰逊，并与他育有一儿一女。二人于1956年离婚。<ref name=nytimesobit /><ref name=guardianobit /> 1971年，弗吉尼亚·约翰逊嫁给了威廉·马斯特斯，那时候马斯特斯已与他第一任妻子离婚。尽管约翰逊和马斯特斯在1993年离婚，但他们仍旧继续着职业上的合作。<ref name=guardianobit /> 约翰逊于2013年因为“多种疾病并发症”逝世。<ref>{{dead link|date=August 2013}} {{cite web |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/news/us/article/Virginia-Johnson-renowned-sex-researcher-dies-4686383.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-07-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130725230317/http://www.seattlepi.com/news/us/article/Virginia-Johnson-renowned-sex-researcher-dies-4686383.php |archivedate=2013-07-25 |df= }}. ''[[Seattle_Post-Intelligencer|Seattle Post-Intelligencer]]''.</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sorkin, Michael D. |url=http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/obituaries/virginia-johnson-masters-dies-at-famed-researcher-helped-debunk-sexual/article_7e76f330-e148-5cea-bae0-af9d51f99310.html |title=Virginia Johnson Masters Dies at 88; Famed Researcher Helped Debunk Sexual Myths |work=[[St._Louis_Post-Dispatch|St. Louis Post-Dispatch]] |date=July 25, 2013 |accessdate=August 10, 2013 |archive-date=2018-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702063045/https://www.stltoday.com/news/local/obituaries/virginia-johnson-masters-dies-at-famed-researcher-helped-debunk-sexual/article_7e76f330-e148-5cea-bae0-af9d51f99310.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

马斯特斯在和约翰逊离婚后又再婚了，<ref name=nytimesobit /> 他于2001年逝世。<ref>{{cite news |first=Richard |last=Severo |title=William H. Masters, a Pioneer in Studying and Demystifying Sex, Dies at 85 |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F07E2DB1E30F93AA25751C0A9679C8B63 |quote=Dr. William H. Masters, who with his co-researcher, Virginia E. Johnson, revolutionized the way sex is studied, taught and enjoyed in America, died Friday at a hospice in Tucson. He was 85 and had lived in retirement since 1994, first in St. Louis and then in Tucson. He suffered complications from Parkinson's disease, said his wife, Geraldine Baker Oliver Masters. |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=February 19, 2001 |accessdate=July 24, 2008 |archive-date=2012-05-27 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120527092010/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F07E2DB1E30F93AA25751C0A9679C8B63 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

